info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 26 at 11:33PM PST until December 27 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 1 PM PST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...San Juan County, Western Whatcom County, Western Skagit County, Admiralty Inlet Area and Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca zones. * WHEN...From 8 AM to 1 PM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong winds could drive waters upward even further depending on where the strongest winds set up.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
